The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques for line segment extraction, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of the Hough transform for this task, which is a well-known technique in robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM) applications. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach that incorporates connectivity in the voting process, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques.
